, and depends very weakly\non $M_{\\star}$ when $\\sigma_{\\star}$ or g-r is fixed. At fixed $M_{star}$, the\n$\\mu_{\\star}$ shows weak correlations with clustering amplitude (and halo mass\nfor central galaxies). Our results suggest that it is necessary to consider\ncentral and satellite galaxies separately when studying the link between\ngalaxies and dark matter halos. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2015 02:10:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 Jan 2016 08:14:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-16"}
