e very similar (except in the very\nneutron-rich fragments), and $T_{IB}$ from IMFs in the $^{124, 136}$Xe and\n$^{112,124}$Sn reactions is also similar. A slightly dependence of $T_{IB}$ on\n$A$ is found. \\item[Conclusions] Using the binding energy of the nucleus,\n$T_{IB}$ can be obtained without the knowledge of the free energies of\nfragments. In the investigated reactions, $T_{IB}$ from most of the IMFs is\nlow.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2015 02:57:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-04"}
